                <div class="path-steps">
                  <div class="path-step neutral">
                    <strong>Doubt:</strong> "I see a spot!"
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step neutral">
                    <strong>DIY Test:</strong> "It grew mold!"
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step warning">
                    <strong>Panic & Misinterpretation:</strong> "I have toxic mold!"
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step warning">
                    <strong>Action:</strong> Call a remediation-only company.
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step danger">
                    <strong>Result:</strong> $5,000+ for unnecessary <a href="/restoration/mold-remediation" class="inline-link-light">remediation</a>, and the *source* (e.g., a pipe leak) is never fixed.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Smart Path -->
              <div class="decision-path success-path">
                <h4 class="path-title success">The Smart Investigation Path</h4>
                <div class="path-steps">
                  <div class="path-step neutral">
                    <strong>Doubt:</strong> "I see a spot!"
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step neutral">
                    <strong>Investigation:</strong> "Where is the moisture?"
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step info">
                    <strong>Informed Diagnosis:</strong> "The spot is small, but it's near a leaky pipe."
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step info">
                    <strong>Action:</strong> Call a plumber *or* a certified <a href="/restoration/mold-remediation/mold-inspection" class="inline-link-light">mold inspector</a> (not remediator) for a real assessment.
                  </div>
                  <div class="path-arrow">↓</div>
                  <div class="path-step success">
                    <strong>Result:</strong> $200 to fix the <a href="/restoration/water-damage/leak-repair" class="inline-link-light">leak</a> and $50 for cleanup. Problem solved at the source.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Steps Section -->
      <section id="steps" class="guide-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-intro">
            <span class="badge badge-teal">The Responsible Homeowner's Plan</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">Start a Smart Investigation</h2>
            <p class="section-description">
              Gaining trust starts with a proper investigation. Use this as your guide *before* you buy a kit or call a professional.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="content-card">
            <ol class="steps-list">
              <li class="step-item">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h4 class="step-title">Follow Your Nose & Eyes</h4>
                  <p>A musty, earthy smell is a major red flag for hidden mold. Visually inspect areas with high humidity: under sinks, in basements, around windows, and in bathrooms. Look for water stains, discoloration, or peeling paint. If you discover <a href="/restoration/water-damage" class="inline-link">water damage</a>, address it immediately.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="step-item">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h4 class="step-title">Find the Water Source</h4>
                  <p>Mold cannot grow without moisture. Your primary goal is not to find the mold, but to find the *water*. Check for leaky pipes, <a href="/restoration/storm-damage" class="inline-link">roof leaks from storms</a>, <a href="/restoration/water-damage/flood-damage" class="inline-link">flooding</a>, or poor drainage. Fixing the water problem is 90% of the battle.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="step-item">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h4 class="step-title">Use a DIY Kit for... Nothing?</h4>
                  <p>Honestly, they are rarely necessary. If you see mold, you have mold. You don't need a test to confirm it. If you suspect hidden mold (you smell it but can't see it), a DIY test is still the wrong tool. It can't find the source. Learn more about <a href="/blog/professional-mold-testing-cost-guide-2025" class="inline-link">professional testing costs</a>.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="step-item">
                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                  <h4 class="step-title">When to Call a Professional</h4>
                  <p>
                    Call a <strong>Certified Mold Inspector</strong> (not a remediation company) if:
                  </p>
                  <ul class="sub-list">
                    <li>You smell mold but can't find it</li>
                    <li>You had a major <a href="/restoration/water-damage/flood-damage" class="inline-link">flood</a> or <a href="/restoration/water-damage/leak-repair" class="inline-link">leak</a></li>
                    <li>You need proof for a landlord or insurance</li>
                    <li>Family members experience health symptoms at home</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="mt-3">An inspector works for *you* and provides an unbiased report and a plan for fixing the source and <a href="/restoration/mold-remediation" class="inline-link">removing the mold</a>, if necessary.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <!-- CTA Card -->
          <div class="cta-card">
            <h3>Don't Let a $50 Kit Lead to a $5,000 Mistake</h3>
            <p>Our certified inspectors provide comprehensive <a href="/restoration/mold-remediation/mold-inspection" class="inline-link-light">mold inspection services</a> throughout Florida with accurate testing, moisture mapping, and clear remediation protocols.</p>
            <div class="cta-buttons">
              <a href="/contact" class="cta-button primary">Get Professional Inspection</a>
              <a href="/restoration/mold-remediation" class="cta-button secondary">Learn About Remediation</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

